LEX Escrow


"Buyer" is	 a person

"Seller" is A person

"Arbiter" is  a person

"Service Fee" is	aN  amount


The Buyer pays an amount into escrow, appoints the Seller, appoints the Arbiter, and fixes the Service Fee


CLAUSE: Pay Out

The Arbiter may pay from escrow the Service Fee to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the Seller


CLAUSE: Pay Back

The Arbiter may pay from escrow the Service Fee to themselves, and afterwards return the remainder of the escrow to the Buyer


